external_knowledge:
- "shining star" refers to the player with the highest average yards per game;
- "outshines the rest" means having the highest performance metric compared to other players;
- "leading the pack" implies being the top-ranked player.

- 'Victors' refers to teams with the highest number of wins;
- 'Shining brightly' refers to the teams with the most wins, which are listed at the top of the results;
- 'Realm of their locations' refers to the locations where the teams are based.

- "star athletes" refers to players who performed exceptionally well in their most recent game;
- "dazzled the field" means they made a significant impact with their performance;
- "physical attempts" refers to the number of attempts (rushing attempts);
- "passing attempts" refers to the number of pass attempts;
- "total yardage prowess" refers to the sum of yards gained from rushing and passing.

- "sprinted the farthest" refers to the players with the highest total yards gained;
- "cumulative distance" refers to the sum of yards gained by a player across all games;
- "trio" refers to the top 3 players.

- "run the longest distances" refers to the total yards gained by the player;
- "their teams" refers to the team name;
- "the number of games they've played" refers to the count of distinct games;
- "their average yardage per game" refers to the total yards divided by the number of games played.

- "star receivers" refers to players who are known for their receiving skills;
- "shine the brightest" implies the highest performance in terms of average receiving yards per game;
- "carrying their teams forward" is a metaphor for contributing significantly to the team's performance through receiving yards.

- "Shone brightest" refers to the players with the highest average yards per game at home;
- "Home turf" refers to games played where the player's team is the home team;
- "Average yards per game" is calculated by dividing the total yards gained by the number of home games played.

- "Top 5" refers to the highest ranks based on total yards;
- "Corresponding teams" means the teams that have the same rank as the players;
- Performance is measured by total yards gained.
